PREHISTORY,archaeological,,,data/google-drive-pdfs/AmazonBay_Mailu_Papua.pdf,2,THE EMERGENCE OF MAILU AS A CENTRAL PLACE IN THE PREHISTORY OF COASTAL PAPUA G.J. Irwin This work is a thesis submitted for the Degree of Doctor of Philosophy in the Australian National University -February 1977-
Prehistory,archaeological,,,data/google-drive-pdfs/AmazonBay_Mailu_Papua.pdf,5,"ABSTRACT At the close of prehistory, the small Papuan island of Mailu was the location of a settlement that can be described as a central place. It was 'central' in that (1) with respect to the pattern of communications among contemporary sites in the are"
