Prehistoric,archaeological,,,data/google-drive-pdfs/Animal motifs on rock art in Papua and West Papua.pdf,35,"jects depicted on the rocks and the life of the people at that time. The life of people who produced the rock art culture was heavily influenced by their tradition of hunting animals. Therefore, the animal motifs in the prehistoric rock paintings are related to animal hunting rituals called sympathetic magic/hunting magic . The type of game depicted on the walls of caves or on prehistoric cliffs was intended to express the hope of bagging an abund"
Prehistoric,archaeological,,,data/google-drive-pdfs/Animal motifs on rock art in Papua and West Papua.pdf,35,"ion of hunting animals. Therefore, the animal motifs in the prehistoric rock paintings are related to animal hunting rituals called sympathetic magic/hunting magic . The type of game depicted on the walls of caves or on prehistoric cliffs was intended to express the hope of bagging an abundance of game. The figures of the game can also be interpreted as symbols of victory or perhaps as trophies of a successful hunt. Conversely, the depiction of an"
Prehistoric,archaeological,,,data/google-drive-pdfs/Animal motifs on rock art in Papua and West Papua.pdf,35,"increase the chance of success in their next hunt. Both rock art in general and rock art with animal motifs have been seen not only in relation to hunting or shamanism. Garfinkel et al. (2009: 319) have postulated that prehistoric rock art is a cultural context built on a relationship between aspects of behaviour, material culture and a system of ideas which characterize a particular community at a certain time. In this case, the depiction of ani"
